1. create package.json ------ npm init
2. create node modules ------ npm i express
3. create index.js file 
4. import express inside the index.js
5. using express create an application
6. setup port number
7. use json parser for server application
8. install cors ---- npm i cors
9. import cors
10. using cors specify origin to the server(integration)
11. api fetch---- fakestoreapi/products
12. create db and collection in mongodb
13. install mongoose to establish connection between server and mongodb--- npm i mongoose
14. create a folder --Services and create two files
    1)db.js
    2)dataService.js
15. in db.js -- import mongoose to establish connection
16. define connection string
17. create model and schema
18. export model
19. import db in dataService, create a function and export it
20. resolving API requset in index.js 
 
 index+dataService
 Node + MongoDB connection successful..............
21. final step

